{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":3555444,"name":"Carson Miller","username":"carsongmiller","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/c/df705f/{size}.png","created_at":"2025-03-12T20:15:33.752Z","cooked":"<p>My team is using swerve drives, and we’re looking for a good way to implement “nudge” buttons.  By this, I mean a button on our controller that the driver could press to move in a pre-determined direction by a pre-determined distance.  I’ve implemented some code using pathplanner to generate a command at runtime, and it works for moving forwards and reverse, but when trying to modify the code to move left/right, the robot doesn’t move in a straight line–it follows more of an S curve.  Still ending up in the correct pose, but not moving in a straight line to get there, which is required for us.  It’s like the robot <em>has</em> to move straight forward out of its current pose, then quickly turns to move towards its final pose, which is also <em>has</em> to approach from the rear (forming an S shape, or reverse S)</p>
<p>So I guess a few questions:</p>
<ol>
<li>Is the approach I’m currently using a good one?</li>
<li>If so, what am I doing wrong that causes left/right moves to follow an S?</li>
<li>If there’s a better way to achieve what we’re looking for, please let me know!</li>
</ol>
<p>Here is a sample function for nudging the robot left:</p>
<pre><code class="lang-auto">public static void NudgeLeft(SwerveSubsystem swerve, double distance_Feet) {
    var currentPose = swerve.getPose();
    var translation = new Translation2d(
        currentPose.getX() - Units.feetToMeters(distance_Feet) * currentPose.getRotation().getSin(),
        currentPose.getY() + Units.feetToMeters(distance_Feet) * currentPose.getRotation().getCos());

    var targetPose = new Pose2d(translation, currentPose.getRotation());

    var waypoints = PathPlannerPath.waypointsFromPoses(currentPose, targetPose);
    var path = new PathPlannerPath(waypoints, standardConstraints, new IdealStartingState(0, currentPose.getRotation()), new GoalEndState(0, currentPose.getRotation()));

    path.preventFlipping = true;
    var command = AutoBuilder.followPath(path);
    command.addRequirements(swerve);
    command.schedule();
}
</code></pre>","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"posts_count":2,"updated_at":"2025-03-12T20:16:10.974Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":8,"reads":80,"readers_count":79,"score":56.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":495333,"topic_slug":"nudge-left-right-commands-at-runtime","display_username":"Carson Miller","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":71738,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"post_url":"/t/nudge-left-right-commands-at-runtime/495333/1","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null,"can_vote":false},{"id":3555465,"name":"","username":"crueter","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/crueter/{size}/258043_2.png","created_at":"2025-03-12T20:37:39.990Z","cooked":"<p>I’d venture to guess that the “heading”–that is, direction of travel–for your waypoints is wrong.</p>
